Note that for 1\leq k\leq\infty, T\_{f}(r,s,D), m\_{f}(r,s,D), \text{and }N^{(k)}\_{f}(r,s,D) only depend on s up to a bounded term, so sometimes we denote them as T\_{f}(r,D), m\_{f}(r,D), and N^{(k)}\_{f}(r,s,D) when s=1.

